  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your<strong> waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped waxy potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel, and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>shallot</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and let the garlic infuse the olive oil – this is your <strong>garlic & shallot oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into quarters, scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p><p>Dice the<strong> deseeded tomato</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped tomato</strong> and <strong>parsley</strong> to a bowl with the<strong> garlic & shallot oil </strong>(reserve the pan)</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> tomato relish</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season generously with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>cod</strong> to the pan with a knob of<strong> butter</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Add a large knob of<strong> butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pot with the drained potatoes, and crush them lightly with a fork</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-crushed-potatoes-and-tomato-relish/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges</p><p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried cod</strong> over the <strong>crushed potatoes</strong> with the<strong> tomato relish</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
